In the central street 23, a few meters from La Rampa, once again gives light one of the most visited corners of the city. The old gas station, with its original columns and capitals, has been surrounded by lights and gardens to offer a new gastronomic service in an informal, modern and family atmosphere.
Also, a beautiful young araucaria, along with other mature trees, begins to grow as a symbol of a commitment to care for the natural.
Savoring an eclectic kitchen, hundreds of visitors already go daily and choose their food from an extensive menu designed to satisfy the preferences tailored to the different current food trends.

Cuban, Caribbean, Italian, Spanish, Chinese and international cuisines are the starting point to characterize the offers of the new team of chefs and entrepreneurs who have joined to give new life to a project that aims to grow and evolve in search of a sovereign, sustainable and high quality service.

Vegetarians, vegans and celiacs also find dishes tailored to their preferences and needs. In a precise and open dialogue, chefs and chefs are always on hand to adjust to the needs and preferences of each of the clients of 23 and H.
